value.value: b is a generically dependent continuant = Def. b is a continuant that g-depends_on one or more other entities. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [074-001])
p is a process boundary =Def. p is a temporal part of a process & p has no proper temporal parts. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [084-001])
b is a continuant fiat boundary = Def. b is an immaterial entity that is of zero, one or two dimensions and does not include a spatial region as part. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [029-001])
b is a process_profile =Def. there is some process c such that b process_profile_of c (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [093-002])
b is a relational quality = Def. for some independent continuants c, d and for some time t: b quality_of c at t & b quality_of d at t. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [057-001])

definition.value: An individual organism identifier that is used to identify a beneficiary of some health insurance.
A CRID symbol that is sufficent to look up a patient file in a medical record registry.
A measurement unit label is as a label that is part of a scalar measurement datum and denotes a unit of measure.

a directive information entity that describes an intended process endpoint. When part of a plan specification the concretization is realized in a planned process in which the bearer tries to effect the world so that the process endpoint is achieved.
a directive information entity that describes an action the bearer will take

A label is a symbol that is part of some other datum and is used to either partially define  the denotation of that datum or to provide a means for identifying the datum as a member of the set of data with the same label

a data item is an information content entity that is intended to be a truthful statement about something (modulo, e.g., measurement precision or other systematic errors) and is constructed/acquired by a method which reliably tends to produce (approximately) truthful statements.
An information content entity that is a mark(s) or character(s) used as a conventional representation of another entity.
A generically dependent continuant that is about some thing.
An information content entity whose concretizations indicate to their bearer how to realize them in a process.
A data item that is an aggregate of other data items of the same type that have something in common. Averages and distributions can be determined for data sets.

A directive information entity with action specifications and objective specifications as parts that, when concretized, is realized in a process in which the bearer tries to achieve the objectives by taking the actions specified.

2/3/2009 Comment from OBI review.

Action specification not well enough specified.
Conditional specification not well enough specified.
Question whether all plan specifications have objective specifications.

Request that IAO either clarify these or change definitions not to use them
A measurement datum is an information content entity that is a recording of the output of a measurement such as produced by a device.
A textual entity is a part of a manifestation (FRBR sense), a generically dependent continuant whose concretizations are patterns of glyphs intended to be interpreted as words, formulas, etc.
A textual entity intended to identify a particular author
A collection of information content entities intended to be understood together as a whole
an information content entity that is part of a document
A symbol that is part of a CRID and that is sufficient to look up a record from the CRID's registry.
An information content entity that consists of a CRID symbol and additional information about the CRID registry to which it belongs.

A CRID registry is a dataset of CRID records, each consisting of a CRID symbol and additional information which was recorded in the dataset through a assigning a centrally registered identifier process.
A textual entity that denotes a particular in reality.
A centrally registered identifier that denotes a particular specimen on which a laboratory test is intended to be executed or has already been executed.
TODO
An information content entity about the type of the specimen to be used for some laboratory tests.
Une donnée qui est supposée être une proposition vraie à propos du type de l'échantillon pour lequel des tests ont été prescrits.
A measurement datum specifying how much of a person's blood is made of red blood cells.
Une mesure qui spécifie quelle portion du sang d'une personne est composée de cellules rouges.
This measurement datum is a volume/volume measure which compares the volume of hemoglobin in one's blood to the total volume of blood in one's body.
A measurement datum which specifies the amount of hemoglobin in a person's blood.
Une mesure qui spécifie la quantité d'hémoglobine dans le sang d'une personne.
This measurement datum is a mass/volume measure which compares the mass of hemoglobin in one's blood to the total volume of blood in one's body.
A data item intended to be a truthful statement about the sampling method used to extract a sample from an entity.
Une donnée supposée être une proposition vraie à propos de la méthode d'échantillonnage utilisée pour extraire un échantillon particulier d'une entité.
A measurement datum specifying the average size of a person's red blood cells.
Une mesure qui spécifie la taille moyenne des cellules rouges d'une personne.

label.value: résultat de volume moyen des plaquettes

definition.value: A measurement datum specifying the average size of the platetels in a person's blood.
Une mesure qui spécifie la taille moyenne des plaquette du sang d'une personne.
A measurement datum which specifies the number of platelet cells in a person's blood.
Une mesure qui spécifie le nombre de plaquettes dans le sang d'une personne.

label.value: résultat de dénombrement de cellules rouges

definition.value: A measurement datum which specifies the number of red blood cell in a person's blood.
Une mesure qui spécifie le nombre de cellules rouges dans le sang d'une personne.

label.value: résultat de variation de taille des cellules rouges

definition.value: A measurement datum which specifies the range of variation of the size of red blood cell in a person's blood.
Une mesure qui spécifie l'étendue de la variation de la taille des cellules rouges dans le sang d'une personne.
